
🎯 Use Case & Problem Framing (GenAI Architect)
📌 Overview

This section defines how to identify and frame GenAI use cases using industry-standard architecture patterns, independent of any single vendor.

It aligns with:

Cloud architecture best practices (AWS, Azure, GCP)

LLM application frameworks (LangChain, LlamaIndex)

Responsible AI guidelines (multi-cloud + open standards)

🧠 1. When to Use GenAI vs Traditional ML
✅ Use GenAI When:

Working with unstructured or semi-structured data

Text, PDFs, emails, chat logs

Tasks require:

Natural language understanding (NLU)

Natural language generation (NLG)

The system benefits from contextual reasoning

Output can tolerate probabilistic variation

❌ Avoid GenAI When:

Deterministic outputs are required

Problem is structured/tabular prediction

Strict auditability and explainability is mandatory

Ultra-low latency systems (<100ms hard constraints)

